# Angular Material 18+ Theme Guidelines

## ⚠️ CRITICAL DISCOVERY: THEME APPLICATION IS MANDATORY

**MOST CRITICAL ISSUE**: Having `@include mat.core()` is NOT ENOUGH. Angular Material components will be **completely unstyled** without an actual theme applied.

### REQUIRED THEME APPLICATION

**Use Azure Blue Material 3 Theme (Angular 18+ Standard)**
```scss
@use '@angular/material' as mat;
@include mat.core();

// CRITICAL: Apply azure-blue Material 3 theme - THIS IS WHAT WAS MISSING
@import '@angular/material/prebuilt-themes/azure-blue.css';
```

### Azure Blue Theme Requirements
- **Theme File**: `azure-blue.css` (70KB Material 3 theme)
- **Location**: `node_modules/@angular/material/prebuilt-themes/azure-blue.css`
- **Type**: Material 3 design tokens with modern CSS custom properties

### Symptoms of Missing Theme Application
- ✅ `@include mat.core()` present but components look like plain HTML
- ❌ CSS bundle size is tiny (~10KB instead of ~100KB)
- ❌ "Could not find Angular Material core theme" warning in console
- ❌ Material components (`mat-card`, `mat-button`, `mat-form-field`) have no styling
- ❌ No Material Design colors, typography, spacing, or visual hierarchy

## CRITICAL THEME ARCHITECTURE REQUIREMENTS

⚠️ **STOP**: Angular Material 18+ uses CSS Custom Properties - DO NOT use legacy theming approaches:

### Modern Theme Architecture Checklist
- [x] Core Material included: `@include mat.core()`
- [x] CSS Custom Properties defined for Material 3 design tokens
- [x] Angular Material handles all component styling automatically
- [x] NO component-level border styling
- [x] NO custom form field styling
- [x] NO custom checkbox styling
- [x] Let Angular Material handle all component theming

### MODERN APPROACH: CSS Custom Properties (Angular 18+)

**CORRECT Implementation - Let Angular Material handle everything**:
```scss
@use '@angular/material' as mat;
@include mat.core();

/* CSS Custom Properties - Angular Material 18+ automatically generates these */
:root {
  --mat-sys-primary: #6750a4;
  --mat-sys-on-primary: #ffffff;
  --mat-sys-surface: #fffbfe;
  --mat-sys-on-surface: #1c1b1f;
  --mat-sys-outline: #79747e;
  /* Angular Material automatically handles all component styling */
}
```

**PROHIBITED - Legacy approaches that cause styling conflicts**:
```scss
/* ❌ DO NOT USE - Material 2 legacy approach */
$primary-palette: mat.define-palette(mat.$indigo-palette);
@include mat.all-component-themes($light-theme);

/* ❌ DO NOT USE - Custom component styling */
.mat-form-field { border: 1px solid #ccc; }
.mat-checkbox { border: 1px solid #999; }
```

## COMPONENT STYLING RULES

⚠️ **CRITICAL**: Angular Material 18+ handles ALL component styling automatically. DO NOT override:

### Input Fields and Form Controls
```scss
/* ✅ CORRECT - Let Angular Material handle form fields */
.mat-form-field {
  /* No custom styling needed - Angular Material handles everything */
  width: 100%;
  margin-bottom: var(--mat-sys-spacing-md, 16px);
}

/* ❌ PROHIBITED - Custom border styling */
.mat-form-field-appearance-outline {
  border: 1px solid var(--mat-sys-outline); /* DON'T DO THIS */
}
```

### Checkboxes and Selection Controls
```scss
/* ✅ CORRECT - Let Angular Material handle checkboxes */
.mat-checkbox {
  /* No custom styling needed - Angular Material handles everything */
}

/* ❌ PROHIBITED - Custom checkbox styling */
.mat-checkbox-frame {
  border: 1px solid var(--mat-sys-outline); /* DON'T DO THIS */
}
```

### Sidebar and Layout Borders
```scss
/* ✅ CORRECT - Let Angular Material handle layout borders */
.mat-sidenav {
  /* No custom border styling needed */
}

/* ❌ PROHIBITED - Custom sidebar borders */
.mat-sidenav {
  border-right: 1px solid var(--mat-sys-outline); /* DON'T DO THIS */
}
```

## NESTED OBJECTS AND DOUBLE BORDER PREVENTION

### Problem: Double Borders
**Root Cause**: Custom CSS competing with Angular Material's built-in styling

**Solution**: Remove ALL custom border styling and let Angular Material handle it

```scss
/* ❌ CAUSES DOUBLE BORDERS */
@media (prefers-contrast: high) {
  .sidenav {
    border-right-width: 2px; /* Conflicts with Angular Material */
  }
}

/* ✅ CORRECT - Let Angular Material handle contrast */
@media (prefers-contrast: high) {
  /* Angular Material automatically adjusts contrast - no custom styling needed */
}
```

## THEME-BASED STYLING BEST PRACTICES

### Use System Variables Only
```scss
/* ✅ CORRECT - Use CSS custom properties */
.my-component {
  background-color: var(--mat-sys-surface);
  color: var(--mat-sys-on-surface);
  border-color: var(--mat-sys-outline); /* Only for custom elements */
}

/* ❌ PROHIBITED - Hardcoded colors */
.my-component {
  background-color: #ffffff;
  color: #000000;
  border: 1px solid #cccccc;
}
```

### Semantic Color Utilities
```scss
/* ✅ CORRECT - Application-specific semantic colors */
.status-success { color: var(--app-success) !important; }
.status-warning { color: var(--app-warning) !important; }
.status-error { color: var(--mat-sys-error) !important; }
```

## COMPONENT SCSS REQUIREMENTS

⚠️ **CRITICAL**: NO component-level styling for Angular Material components

### What Components Should NOT Include
```scss
/* ❌ PROHIBITED in component SCSS files */

// Custom form field styling
.mat-form-field-appearance-outline { /* Any styling */ }

// Custom checkbox styling  
.mat-checkbox-frame { /* Any styling */ }

// Custom sidebar borders
.mat-sidenav { border: /* Any border styling */; }

// Custom button borders
.mat-raised-button { border: /* Any border styling */; }
```

### What Components CAN Include
```scss
/* ✅ ALLOWED in component SCSS files */

// Layout and spacing
.my-container {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--mat-sys-spacing-md, 16px);
}

// Application-specific styling
.status-indicator {
  background-color: var(--app-success);
  padding: 4px 8px;
  border-radius: 4px;
}

// Typography using Material tokens
.my-text {
  color: var(--mat-sys-on-surface);
  font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;
}
```

