## FLUID DESIGN AND RESPONSIVE THEMING (2024/2025 BEST PRACTICES)

### Material 3 Design Tokens for Fluid Layouts

**✅ CORRECT - Fluid Design with Material 3 Tokens**:
```scss
// Use Material 3 spacing tokens with clamp() for fluid responsiveness
.container {
  padding: clamp(
    var(--mat-sys-spacing-sm, 8px),
    2vw,
    var(--mat-sys-spacing-lg, 24px)
  );
  gap: clamp(
    var(--mat-sys-spacing-xs, 4px),
    1.5vw,
    var(--mat-sys-spacing-md, 16px)
  );
}

// Fluid typography using Material 3 type scale
.heading {
  font-size: clamp(
    var(--mat-sys-typescale-headline-small-size),
    4vw,
    var(--mat-sys-typescale-headline-large-size)
  );
}
```

**❌ PROHIBITED - Fixed Values Without Theme Integration**:
```scss
/* DON'T DO THIS - Breaks theme consistency */
.container {
  padding: 16px; // Fixed value ignores theme
  gap: 12px; // No Material token usage
}

.heading {
  font-size: 24px; // Hardcoded size
}
```

### Responsive Grid Layouts with Material Theming

**✅ CORRECT - Theme-Aware Grid Systems**:
```scss
// Grid that respects Material 3 spacing system
.dashboard-grid {
  display: grid;
  gap: var(--mat-sys-spacing-md, 16px);
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(
    calc(250px + var(--mat-sys-spacing-md, 16px)),
    1fr
  ));
  
  // Container queries with Material tokens
  container-type: inline-size;
  
  @container (max-width: 480px) {
    gap: var(--mat-sys-spacing-sm, 8px);
  }
}
```

### Full-Width Layouts with Material 3

**✅ MODERN APPROACH - Remove Layout Constraints**:
```scss
// Let content breathe on large screens
.mat-sidenav-content {
  // Remove max-width constraints
  .content-wrapper {
    width: 100%;
    // Only constrain text for readability
    .text-content {
      max-width: 65ch;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
  }
}

// Admin dashboards use full viewport
.admin-dashboard {
  width: 100%;
  padding: clamp(
    var(--mat-sys-spacing-md, 16px),
    3vw,
    var(--mat-sys-spacing-xl, 32px)
  );
}
```

### Material 3 Surface Containers for Responsive Design

**✅ USE Material 3 Surface Containers**:
```scss
// Responsive cards with proper elevation
.dashboard-card {
  background: var(--mat-sys-surface-container);
  border-radius: var(--mat-sys-shape-corner-large);
  padding: clamp(
    var(--mat-sys-spacing-md, 16px),
    3vw,
    var(--mat-sys-spacing-lg, 24px)
  );
  
  // Elevation on hover
  transition: box-shadow 200ms ease-in-out;
  
  &:hover {
    box-shadow: var(--mat-sys-elevation-3);
  }
}
```

### Responsive Spacing System Integration

**✅ IMPLEMENT - Dynamic Spacing Classes**:
```scss
// Generate responsive spacing utilities
@each $size, $value in (
  'xs': var(--mat-sys-spacing-xs, 4px),
  'sm': var(--mat-sys-spacing-sm, 8px),
  'md': var(--mat-sys-spacing-md, 16px),
  'lg': var(--mat-sys-spacing-lg, 24px),
  'xl': var(--mat-sys-spacing-xl, 32px)
) {
  .gap-#{$size} {
    gap: clamp(
      calc(#{$value} * 0.75),
      2vw,
      calc(#{$value} * 1.25)
    );
  }
  
  .p-#{$size} {
    padding: clamp(
      calc(#{$value} * 0.75),
      2vw,
      calc(#{$value} * 1.25)
    );
  }
}
```

### Key Integration Points

1. **Always Use Material Tokens**: Never hardcode spacing or colors
2. **Fluid First**: Use clamp() with Material tokens for responsive scaling
3. **Remove Constraints**: Let admin interfaces use full screen width
4. **Container Queries**: Modern responsive design at component level
5. **Theme Consistency**: All responsive utilities must use Material 3 tokens

